data.description:
xUnit.net is a developer testing framework, built to support Test Driven Development, with a design goal of extreme simplicity and alignment with framework features.

Installing this package installs xunit.core, xunit.assert, and xunit.analyzers.
data.summary: xUnit.net is a developer testing framework, built to support Test Driven Development.
data.title: xUnit.net

data.description: Code Analyzers for projects using xUnit.net that help find and fix frequent issues when writing tests.
data.title: xUnit.net [Code Analyzers]

data.description: Common abstractions used to exchange information between xUnit.net and version-independent runners (xunit.abstractions.dll).
data.summary: Common abstractions used to exchange information between xUnit.net and version-independent runners (xunit.abstractions.dll).
data.title: xUnit.net [Abstractions]

data.description: Includes the assertion library from xUnit.net (xunit.assert.dll). Supports .NET Standard 1.1.
data.summary: Includes the assertion library from xUnit.net (xunit.assert.dll).
data.title: xUnit.net [Assertion Library]

data.description: Includes the libraries for writing unit tests with xUnit.net.
data.summary: Includes the libraries for writing unit tests with xUnit.net.
data.title: xUnit.net [Core Unit Testing Framework]

data.description: Includes xunit.core.dll for extensibility purposes. Supports .NET 4.5.2 or later, and .NET Standard 1.1.
data.title: xUnit.net [Extensibility: Core]

data.description: Includes xunit.execution.*.dll for extensibility purposes. Supports .NET 4.5.2 or later, and .NET Standard 1.1.
data.title: xUnit.net [Extensibility: Execution]

data.description: Visual Studio 2012+ Test Explorer runner for the xUnit.net framework. Capable of running xUnit.net v1.9.2 and v2.0+ tests. Supports .NET 2.0 or later, .NET Core 1.0 or later, and Universal Windows 10.0 or later.
data.title: xUnit.net [Runner: Visual Studio]

data.description: Console runner for the xUnit.net framework. Capable of running xUnit.net v1.9.2 and v2.0+ tests. Supports .NET 4.5.2 or later, .NET Core 1.x, and .NET Core 2.x.
data.summary: Console runner for the xUnit.net framework.
data.title: xUnit.net [Runner: Console]

data.description: .NET CLI SDK runner for the xUnit.net framework. Supports .NET 4.5.2 or later, .NET Core 1.x, and .NET Core 2.x.
data.summary: .NET CLI SDK runner for the xUnit.net framework.
data.title: xUnit.net [Runner: .NET CLI SDK]

data.description: Includes the version-independent runner for xUnit.net to run both v1.9.2 and v2.0+ tests (xunit.runner.utility.*.dll). Supports .NET 3.5, .NET 4.5.2 or later, .NET Standard 1.1, .NET Standard 1.5, UWP, and .NET Core 1.0 or later.
data.summary: Includes the version-independent runner for xUnit.net (xunit.runner.utility.*.dll).
data.title: xUnit.net [Runner Utility]

data.description: Package to use SpecFlow with xUnit 2.4 and later
data.summary: Package to use SpecFlow with xUnit 2.4 and later
data.title: SpecFlow.xUnit

data.description: Includes runner reporters for TeamCity, AppVeyor, Verbose and Quiet output for test runners. Supports .NET 4.5.2 or later, .NET Standard 1.1, .NET Standard 1.5, and .NET Core 1.0 or later.
data.summary: Includes runner reporters: TeamCity, AppVeyor, Verbose and Quiet.
data.title: xUnit.net [Runner Reporters]

data.description: MSBuild runner for the xUnit.net framework. Capable of running xUnit.net v1.9.2 and v2.0+ tests. Supports .NET 4.5.2 or later.
data.summary: MSBuild runner for the xUnit.net framework.
data.title: xUnit.net [Runner: MSBuild]

data.description: NOTE: This empty package exists to assist users upgrading from xUnit.net v1.x to v2.x.
data.title: xUnit.net [Extensions]

data.description:
A very extensive set of extension methods that allow you to more naturally specify the expected outcome of a TDD or
      BDD-style unit tests. Targets .NET Framework 4.5 and 4.7, as well as .NET Core 2.0, .NET Core 3.0, .NET Core 2.1, .NET Standard 1.3, 1.6, 2.0 and 2.1.
      Supports the unit test frameworks MSTest, MSTest2, Gallio, NUnit, XUnit, MBUnit, MSpec, and NSpec.
data.title: FluentAssertions

data.description: NOTE: This empty package exists to assist users upgrading from xUnit.net v1.x to v2.x.
data.title: xUnit.net [Runners]

data.description: By leveraging the data theory feature of xUnit.net, this extension turns AutoFixture into a declarative framework for writing unit tests. In many ways it becomes a unit testing DSL (Domain Specific Language).
data.title: AutoFixture with xUnit.net v2 data theories

data.description: Make your Xunit test methods self-determine to report a "skipped" result. Useful for such cases as "not supported on this platform" results or other environmental inputs.
data.title: Dynamic test skipping for Xunit

data.description:
FsCheck.Xunit integrates FsCheck with xUnit.NET by adding a PropertyAttribute that runs FsCheck tests, similar to xUnit.NET's FactAttribute.

All the options normally available in vanilla FsCheck via configuration can be controlled via the PropertyAttribute.
data.title: FsCheck.Xunit
